      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARA'S GHOST (4) was a winner two back then strongly fancied last time but could only manage a second (28.62) at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. One of the leading chances. CAWBOURNE SLICK (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (29.11) at this track behind Assassino in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from five starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. CANYA HELLFIRE (5) struggled in tougher grade last start after losing his position early at Rockhampton, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Q Lakeside (25.78) beating Sagacious Syd in a Grade 5 on May 19. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. PHOENIX SILVER (7) is worth consideration after filling a hole at this course and distance last start.",
